Working. Here's the quick cheat sheet:

**Both tools take all-optional args** — an empty call (`{}`) is the same as `*_list`.

```jsonc
// Substring across title + body (case-insensitive)
mcp__panopt__todo_search { "query": "search" }

// Combine filters — all conditions AND together
mcp__panopt__todo_search {
  "query": "terminal",
  "status": "open",
  "priority": "high"
}

// Find unassigned todos (empty string = "no assignee")
mcp__panopt__todo_search { "assignee": "" }

// Tag AND — both tags must be present
mcp__panopt__todo_search { "tags": ["bug", "frontend"] }

// Scratchpads only support query + tags
mcp__panopt__scratchpad_search { "query": "terminal" }
mcp__panopt__scratchpad_search { "tags": ["design"] }
```

**Live results from your DB just now:**
- `query: "search"` → found todo #33 (this one), #46 (universal object search), plus #17 ("memories") and #94 because both bodies happen to contain the word "search".
- `status: "in_progress"` → `[]` (nothing in progress — #33 flipped to `completed` when I called `todo_complete`).
- `scratchpad_search query: "todo"` → 4 scratchpads whose body mentions "todo".

**Field reference:**
- `status`: `open` / `in_progress` / `backlog` / `draft` / `completed` / `not_done` — anything else → `invalid_params` error.
- `priority`: `high` / `medium` / `low`.
- `assignee`: case-insensitive exact match; `""` = unassigned.
- `tags`: AND semantics. Omitting or `[]` skips the filter.
- `query`: substring against `title` OR `body`, lower-cased on both sides.

Return shape mirrors `todo_list` / `scratchpad_list` exactly, so wherever you use those today you can drop in the search variant.

